Vol / Page:  256/8/4
Edition:
Quote:  We now and again,. . .,hear a great deal about the reforming influences of present-day gaol systems, which fondly aim at effecting complete reformation in the evil doer by keeping him gaoled for life as an habitual criminal. incidentally, a candidate for the `Kathleen Mavourneen Stakes,' in the person of one Charles William Nicholson appeared ... in Wellington's Magistrate's Court on Saturday and Monday last.
